# RoForest Mobile — environment variables
#
# Copy this to .env.local for personal dev overrides.
# Files matching .env*.local are gitignored.
#
# All vars must be prefixed with EXPO_PUBLIC_ to be readable in client code.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Backend URL
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# This MUST be reachable from the device running the app.
#
# Localhost only works on the iOS simulator. A real iPhone/Android phone
# needs your Mac's LAN IP, or an Expo tunnel URL.
#
# To find your Mac's LAN IP:
#   ipconfig getifaddr en0    # Wi-Fi interface (most common)
#   ipconfig getifaddr en1    # Ethernet, if applicable
#
# Then make sure your dev server (cd .. && npm run dev) listens on 0.0.0.0,
# not just localhost — check server/index.ts.
#
# Examples:
#   EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:5000          # iOS simulator
#   EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://192.168.1.42:5000       # Real device on same Wi-Fi
#   EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://abc-xyz.exp.direct      # Expo tunnel (slow but works anywhere)
#   EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://roforest.ro             # Production
#
EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:5000
